The Daily Green is a diner-style eatery built into a charming old building downtown -  that apparently used to be some sort of drive-through.  The Daily Green has it’s own vibe. It’s a good vibe, but you may want to know what you’re getting into. This place serves food with an emphasis on local sourcing and dietary accommodations. There are plenty of options for vegans, gluten-free folk and omnivores.  They don’t like to stress in here, so you may be waiting a little longer than you would expect. And the prices are a bit higher than is usual for Gainesville, but the local sourcing of ingredients probably causes that.  Despite it’s quirks (or because of them) Daily Green easily earns full marks and deserves a prominent position in the Gainesville food scene.

We got the Falafel Nachos and the Avocado Stack as well as a side of Vegan Grits. I don't think either of us had a single complaint or critique about the food. Even if we had one, we were too busy stuffing our faces to verbalize it. This is what vegan food is supposed to be. Not a reheated frozen entree or vegan options thrown on a menu as an after-thought. But instead, Daily Green provides wholesome, tasty vegan dishes that are nutritional and satisfying. We would be happy to come back here often to enjoy the other great menu items they offer.

Daily Green is by far the most healthful, creative, delicious restaurant in North Central Florida, serving the greatest amount of organic food than any other restaurant in the area. They have something for everyone. From gluten free, to vegan, to meat eaters. My favorite time to go is Sunday for their brunch menu. I always get the veggie Benedict, but am also a huge fan of their grit cakes, gritlin rancheros, tempeh scramble, and of course their bottomless mimosas (made with fresh squeezed oranges). If you have a group of people who all have a sweet tooth, their waffle towers are incredible both to eat and look at (and gluten free). Their regular weekly menu is also amazing. Say you see a sandwich that you like, but aren't wanting bread that day...you can modify it to be put on a collard wrap, tortilla (gf or reg), or even in a waffle cone (gf)! My favorite weekday menu options are the raw nachos, the tempeh ru sandwich, and the thai peanut tempeh salad. This place has absolutely perfected the art of making healthy food taste good. Most all of their desserts are gluten free and vegan. The taste of these desserts isn't compromised in any way, in fact I've had some of the best desserts I've ever had here AND you feel good afterwards. I could rant and rave about this place all day and want to reiterate on the fact that ANYONE can find something they like here, including people who have a lot of food restrictions. They serve kombucha on tap, along with beer, and craft draft nitro coffee. They also have a large variety of other drinks including house made tonics, fresh juice, and smoothies. This place definitely puts a ton of love in every plate served, and I highly recommend it to anyone.
Please come here the food is AWESOME!!
Amazing Vegan and Gluten free options, one of the only places I can actually eat. Just go eat here now,  best food in Gainesville.

This is my go to Lunch spot! No words describe how good the food is. The best part is it caters to variety of diets- vegan, vegetarian, meat-eaters and I think, I am not sure they have also options for the gluten free. It's fresh, made with the best of the ingredients and made with love- you can feel it when you eat their food. Just go try it. And the best part-it's as local as it's gonna get!

This place is the best kept secret in Gainesville. As a student, I know that my friends don't like to venture out Of the chipotle/Starbucks/pizza outings...I tell them for the same money (10 dollars) they can have the best chicken salad sandwich of their life and a side of Mac and cheese. Everything I've tried on the menu is fresh and tasty. My only complaint is that the staff gets visibly overwhelmed and sometimes unprofessional when they are busy. I took my mom for brunch and they gave me three separate plates before getting my Order right. Of course, the food is still amazing. Thank you daily green.
Amazing!!!

I LOVE Daily Green! Super vegetarian/vegan friendly yet also serving plenty to please the meat-eater, this restaurant exists in an old building that they renovated. The inside is small (so get there early to get a seat!) but comfortable and the staff is very friendly and patient (for those of us who can never decide what they want!). There is plenty of parking in the lot or on the street.  They feature a regular menu plus a specials board that always has something new and exciting on it. I was impressed with the creativity yet simplicity of the menu. The food is so delicious and fresh, and you get a lot of it.  I was very full and could barely finish my walnut lentil burger and broccoli side!  But that's OK, because what you don't finish either gets composted or made into grub to serve to the pigs at the local Siembra farm! I loved this and think it's such a great way to reuse food waste. Nearly everything there is recycle or reused rather than thrown away. It makes you feel good about eating there.  They are closed Monday and Tuesday, but they do offer weekend brunch (though I haven't tried that yet).

My favorite place to eat in Gainesville.  As a vegan there aren't too many options for me food-wise, and this is above and beyond my expectations. They are an eco friendly and conscious business as well, which is really important to me. I couldn't be more pleased with a restaurant.
The food here is varied and delicious. We visit regularly for their Sunday brunch.

I have never failed to be impressed by the food at the Daily Green in the more than a dozen times I have been there. This evening I ordered the temph Ruben and it was absolutely delicious. My friend ordered the savory waffle chicken salad. Both her and I were very impressed. Most restaurants give you a bland mess and call it food. This is not true at the Daily Green, it is always well seasoned and absolutely fresh.
Soul and body nourishment!
The quality of food here (flavor and source) is just excellent. Great for veggies and omnivores alike
Very cool place. A little expensive, but not more expensive than any other organic/vegetarian/local dining place. Very friendly staff. Tasty food.

Had a wonderful experience. Went there with a "Get My Perks" certificate, & they were friendly & helpful, & the food was delicious! With a fabulous selection of vegan, vegetarian, & meat dishes & smoothies! :) Great buttermilk pancakes with real maple syrup, & complimentary watermelon cucumber water. :) I loved it & would recommend it to anyone. It's got beautiful local art on the walls, as well, for very affordable prices :) . Check it out! (Where the old "Loui's" used to be downtown near the fire dept & the CMC.)
Unique & fresh menu. Their food is SO good. Can't wait to go back. :)
